cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.FL 

The paper discusses digital forensic science, which involves computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), cloud computing (cs.DC), cybercrime (cs.CY), software engineering (cs.SE), and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The focus of the paper is on evaluating digital forensic process models in the context of a cloud-based evidence processing paradigm, which involves aspects of all these sub-categories.
